## COMMON PITFALLS

| Pitfall | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Reading entire bulletin files | Use `extract.py` or `search.py` scripts instead |
| Using fiscal year totals for a calendar year question | Find monthly breakdowns and sum |
| Stopping at the first plausible answer | Search newer bulletins too — data is revised |
| Wrong units (millions vs billions) | Always check the table header row |
| Rounding intermediate values | Only round the final result |
| Misreading merged/nested column headers | Read 2–3 header rows from the script output |
| Fiscal year confusion pre-1977 | FY ended June 30 before 1977, September 30 after |
| "Percent difference" ≠ "percent change" | CHANGE = `\|B-A\|/A×100` (base). DIFFERENCE = `\|A-B\|/avg×100` (average). |
| Adding `%` when not asked | Only include `%` if question explicitly asks for it |
| Trailing zeros | Drop them: `27.0` → `27`, `1.200` → `1.2` |

